The convertible roof system market can be segmented by type, vehicle type, and material used in the construction of the roof. The two main types of convertible roofs are hardtop and soft-top roofs. While hardtop roofs provide better insulation and security, soft-top roofs offer a classic and traditional convertible experience. Vehicle type segmentation includes sedans, SUVs, and sports cars, with each segment having varying requirements for convertible roof systems. Finally, the material used in the construction of the roof can be fabric, glass, or plastic, each offering different levels of durability, aesthetics, and functionality.

